                                Assessment
                                Determine that:
                                   (i) the issuing facility verifies that PIV Card issuance has
                                       been authorized by a proper authority and that the
                                       employee’s or contractor’s background investigation is
                                       valid (review, observe);
                                  (ii) Re-investigations are performed if required, in accordance
                                       with OPM guidance (review);
                                 (iii) The issuing facility is able to reconnect the applicant to the
                                       chain-of-trust per [FIPS 201-2] issuance requirements
                                       (observe).
                                 (iv) The issuing facility has alternate procedures to release the
                                       PIV Card when the biometric match is unsuccessful
